Question 1--->Write a program to input two numbers and find the maximum between two numbers using the conditional/ternary operator.
  Answer 1--->

package com.demo;

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Ternarynum{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
                                                                                                           // Create a Scanner object for input
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

                                                                                                         // Input two numbers
        System.out.print("Enter the first number: ");
        int num1 = scanner.nextInt();

        System.out.print("Enter the second number: ");
        int num2 = scanner.nextInt();

                                                                                                         // Find the maximum using the ternary operator
        int max = (num1 > num2) ? num1 : num2;
 
                                                                                                       // Display  max
        System.out.println("The maximum number is: " + max);
        
        // Close the scanner
        scanner.close();
    }
}

    Output:-
    Enter the first number: 20
    Enter the second number: 40
    The maximum number is: 40


Question 2---->Write a program to declare  a variable for integer number.Assign a value to it and shift it to left and right using shift operators.
You can use shift by 1 place,  shift by 2 places.Print output for both left & right shifts.
Answer 2---->


package com.demo;

public class Shiftop {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
                                                                                                                         // Declare an integer variable 
        int number = 68;                                                                                   // Change the value
                                                                                                                        // Left shift by 1 place
        int leftShiftBy1 = number << 1;

                                                                                                                        // Left shift by 2 places
        int leftShiftBy2 = number << 2;

                                                                                                                     // Right shift by 1 place
        int rightShiftBy1 = number >> 1;

                                                                                                                      // Right shift by 2 places
        int rightShiftBy2 = number >> 2;

                                                                                                                       // Print  results
        System.out.println("Original number: " + number);
        System.out.println("Left shift by 1 place: " + leftShiftBy1);
        System.out.println("Left shift by 2 places: " + leftShiftBy2);
        System.out.println("Right shift by 1 place: " + rightShiftBy1);
        System.out.println("Right shift by 2 places: " + rightShiftBy2);
    }
}


     Output:-
      Original number: 68
      Left shift by 1 place: 136
      Left shift by 2 places: 272
      Right shift by 1 place: 34
      Right shift by 2 places: 17
